<div2 type="caption">

<p>Negro Ben v. Sabrett Scott.</p>

</div2>

<div2 type="syllabus">

<p>An affidavit is not necessary to continue negro petitions at the first term.</p>

</div2>

<div2 type="body">
 
<p>The Court will not require in all cases an affidavit at the first term to continue cases of negro petitions.</p>
                
<p>This cause was continued at the cost of the defendant, as the petitioner offered himself ready for trail; and in general the Court will not insist on a trial at the first term, but if either party offers ready, it shall be continued at the cost of the party not ready. At the second term the Court will require a trial unless good cause be shown on affidavit.</p>
 
</div2>

</div1>

